# NestJS Module Patterns

## Adding a feature

Create: `*.module.ts`, `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.repo.ts`, `dto/` folder.

Wire the module in `src/app.module.ts` (or parent module).

## Auth guards and decorators

| Decorator / guard | Use |
|---|---|
| `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` | User JWT (default for protected routes) |
| `@UseGuards(AdminJwtAuthGuard)` | Admin panel routes |
| `@Public()` | Optional JWT — unauthenticated callers allowed |
| `@AllowUnverified()` | Skip phone verification check |
| `@CurrentUser()` | Inject authenticated user from JWT |

## Errors

Throw NestJS exceptions with **i18n keys**, not user-facing strings:

```typescript
throw new ConflictException('PHONE_EXISTS');
throw new UnauthorizedException('INVALID_CREDENTIALS');
```

Add translations in both `src/i18n/en/` and `src/i18n/ar/`.

## Throttling

Use `@AuthThrottle()` or `@StrictAuthThrottle()` on auth endpoints (see `src/common/decorators/auth-throttle.decorator.ts`).
